  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple national and international laws and regulations designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes. Here are key components:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group international cooperation standards\n\n2. United States Regulations\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Act\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- Currency and Foreign Transactions Reporting Act\n\n3. Typical Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n\n4. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Civil penalties\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Financial institution sanctions\n- Individual professional penalties\n\n5. Reporting Obligations\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Large cash transaction documentation\n- International fund transfer reporting\n\n6. Regulatory Agencies\n- Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN)\n- Internal Revenue Service\n- Department of Justice\n- Securities and Exchange Commission\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent financial crimes and track potential illicit monetary activities.",
